`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `ResourceType` extension rippled across 8 test files because TypeScript's `Record<T, number>` requires all keys of `T` to be present in literal objects. The fix pattern — `{ ...emptyResources(), timber: 100 }` — is idiomatic and forward-safe: future resource type additions only require updating `emptyResources()`, not every test callsite.
